<p>

<b>Geralyn Madrigal Gaspar</b>, who is better known by her <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../296/81296.xml">
screen name</link> <b>Ehra Madrigal</b> (born <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../799/15799.xml">
June 25</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../846/34846.xml">
1985</link> in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../223/284223.xml">
Quezon City</link></village>
, <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../440/23440.xml">
Philippines</link></country>
) is a <ethnic_group wordnetid="107967382" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../105/2298105.xml">
Filipina</link></ethnic_group>
 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../753/753.xml">
actress</link>.</p>

<sec>
<st>
Life and career</st>

<p>

Ehra is a talent of <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<performer wordnetid="110415638" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.8">
<entertainer wordnetid="109616922" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../613/3086613.xml">
Annabelle Rama</link></entertainer>
</actor>
</causal_agent>
</performer>
</person>
</physical_entity>
 and is a contract artist of <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../623/2198623.xml">
GMA Network</link></company>
. A high school graduate of <private_school wordnetid="108411170" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../710/11761710.xml">
St. Mary's College, Quezon City</link></private_school>
, she is the eldest sister of fellow actress <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../683/11031683.xml">
Michelle Madrigal</link></actor>
 and the daughter of former actress <link>
Karla Kalua</link>, whose real name is Katherine Ann Madrigal. She, her younger sister Michelle, and her mother are distant relatives of affluent <ethnic_group wordnetid="107967382" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../977/3439977.xml">
Spanish</link></ethnic_group>
-<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../721/360721.xml">
Visayan</link> family, the <link>
Madrigal Family</link>.  After her teenybooper days, she got into a "leading lady" status in GMA Primetime shows like <series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../520/10577520.xml">
Lupin</link></series>
, <series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../681/11239681.xml">
Kamandag</link></series>
 and among others. She becomes a Tanduay calendar girl and model for the year 2008 after <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../289/5870289.xml">
Katrina Halili</link></actor>
. Ehra became 2-time <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://www.fhm.com.ph/fhm-babes/profile/639/ehra-madrigal">
FHM Philippines</weblink> covergirl for September 2006 and June 2008 while her sister Michelle became 1-time FHM covergirl for the same month as Ehra's but in 2007 issue. Aside from being a talent of GMA Network, she has also appeared in the movie My Bestfriend's Girlfriend with Richard Gutierrez and Marian Rivera. </p>
<p>

In an interview with the <weblink xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://supreme.ph">
Philippine Star Supreme</weblink>, Ehra reveals she loves cooking, saying:</p>

<p>

"Specialty ni Michelle beef caldereta. Ako, gusto kong niluluto yung mga sinigang o nilaga. O kaya salmon, bini-bake ko siya at nilalagyan ko ng olive oil na may basil. Mga healthy-healthy food." ("Michelle's specialty is beef caldereta. I like cooking sinigang or nilaga. Or salmon, which i bake with olive oli and basil. Healthy food.")<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>


